				<name type="primary" sortindex="1" value="カードツイクスト (Card Twixt)" />
			
						                           
						               													<description>&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#171;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#188;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#137;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#132;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#164;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#175;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#185;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#136; (Card Twixt) is an expansion to the original game Twixt produced by Japanese Twixt Association (&amp;#230;&amp;#151;&amp;#165;&amp;#230;&amp;#156;&amp;#172;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#132;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#164;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#175;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#185;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#136;&amp;#229;&amp;#141;&amp;#148;&amp;#228;&amp;#188;&amp;#154;). The intent is to help players learn Twixt and explore the different strategies in the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;NOTE: you need a copy of Twixt to be able to use this deck.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players new to Twixt are faced with a blank board and don't know where to start. Card Twixt helps by offering new ways to play. There is a deck of basic rules and introductory rules that explore variants in the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;For example, cards in the basic set might be played to instruct a player where to place their next peg. Or the introductory rules add variants such as starting positions, or removing a bridge piece.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The designers set out to help players learn Twixt but discovered lots more opportunities in the game themselves as they developed Card Twixt.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
